<DCT>BEIJING, <TIMEX3 tid="t0" type="TIME" value="1997-04-03" temporalFunction="false" functionInDocument="CREATION_TIME">April 3 , 1997</TIMEX3> (AFP)</DCT>

<TITLE>Beijing reins in arbitrary fees to attract foreign investment</TITLE>


<TEXT>

China's capital city has <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e1">introduced</EVENT> a "card" system to <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e2">protect</EVENT> foreign investors from officials' arbitrary illegal fees, mayor Lu Yucheng was <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e3">quoted</EVENT> as <EVENT class="REPORTING" eid="e4">saying</EVENT> <TIMEX3 type="DATE" value="1997-04-10" tid="t1">Thursday</TIMEX3>.

The cards, <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e5">issued</EVENT> to foreign-funded enterprises, <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e6">identify</EVENT> a limited list of officially-sacntioned fees and <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e7">give</EVENT> firms the right to <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e8">refuse</EVENT> to <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e9">pay</EVENT> any charge not <EVENT class="REPORTING" eid="e10">cited</EVENT>, he <EVENT class="REPORTING" eid="e11">said</EVENT>.

Only three bodies in the city -- the municipal government, the municipal bureau of finance and the municipal bureau of price -- are <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e12">authorised</EVENT> to <EVENT class="I_ACTION" eid="e13">establish</EVENT> new fees, the report <EVENT class="REPORTING" eid="e14">said</EVENT>.

Investors in China have long <EVENT class="I_ACTION" eid="e15">complained</EVENT> of cost overruns <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e16">caused</EVENT> by local officials' legion unpredictable fees.

Though government policy has <EVENT class="I_ACTION" eid="e17">sought</EVENT> to <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e18">attract</EVENT> investment, the practices of corrupt individual administrators and departments often <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e19">undermine</EVENT> the effort.

Three centres have been <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e21">set</EVENT> up in the city to <EVENT class="OCCURRENCE" eid="e22">receive</EVENT> foreign investors' complaints, Lu <EVENT class="REPORTING" eid="e24">said</EVENT>.

</TEXT>


